CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 17, 1946, pg.17 reads: "Mother And Child - Charming Mrs. Theodore Coleman and her son were visitors in Pittsburgh last week with her husband, the widely known writer, who is now on the Chicago Edition staff of the Pittsburgh Courier. Mrs. Coleman is the former Miss Frances Moore.  The youngster, who has already started training for newspaper work, is named Theodore Leslie Coleman Jr.  The Colemans were fated by their many friends during Frog Week. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Frances Moore Coleman wearing two toned dress, seated in armchair, holding Theodore Leslie Coleman Jr. in domestic interior
